    "body": "Hey @drortirosh, thanks a lot for suggesting this. As @djh58 said, the workaround for now is to set `networks.hardhat.chainId` in the config. There are also some shenanigans you can do with environment variables to be able to change the chain id from the command line (I can expand on this if you want).\r\n\r\nWe are planning to make a `hardhat-network-cli` binary to let users start a hardhat network instance outside of a hardhat project. That command will have several parameters like this. I wonder though how to call a \"use the same id as the remote network\" param. Since that's a somewhat unsafe thing to do (for replay reasons), we don't want to do it by default, nor to make it _too_ easy to do. Maybe a verbose param like `--unsafe-use-remote-chain-id` could work.",
