    "body": "I don't think it's particularly unsafe, but I'm not a security guy so take it with a grain of salt.\r\n\r\nThe way I understand the problem is: if someone somehow has access to the transactions you are sending to Hardhat, and you are using a real account with funds (which you maybe shouldn't?), and the attacker somehow benefits from those txs (or just wants to troll you I guess), then they could take those txs and replay them in the real chain. Does that make sense?",
